data.ipq: What's up?==NEW-LINE==What's new?==NEW-LINE==What have you been up to lately?==NEW-LINE==How's it going?==NEW-LINE==How are things?==NEW-LINE==How's life?
I'm fine, thanks. How about you?==NEW-LINE==Pretty good.==NEW-LINE==Same as always==NEW-LINE==Not so great.==NEW-LINE==Could be better==NEW-LINE==cant complain==NEW-LINE==

I really appreciate it.==NEW-LINE==I'm really grateful==NEW-LINE==That's so kind of you.==NEW-LINE==I owe you one. (this means you want/need to do a favor for the other person in the future)==NEW-LINE==
No problem.==NEW-LINE==No worries==NEW-LINE==Don't mention it.==NEW-LINE==My pleasure.==NEW-LINE==Anytime.==NEW-LINE==
It was nice chatting with you.==NEW-LINE==Anyway, I should get going.==NEW-LINE==

Do you have any idea…?==NEW-LINE==Would you happen to know…? (when you're not sure if the other person has the information.)==NEW-LINE==I don't suppose you (would) know…? (when you're not sure if the other person has the information.)==NEW-LINE==
I have no idea/clue.==NEW-LINE==I can't help you there.==NEW-LINE==(informal) Beats me.==NEW-LINE==I'm not really sure.==NEW-LINE==I've been wondering that, too.==NEW-LINE==
I've never given it much thought.==NEW-LINE==I don't have strong feelings either way.==NEW-LINE==It doesn't make any difference to me.==NEW-LINE==I have no opinion on the matter.==NEW-LINE==

Exactly.==NEW-LINE==Absolutely.==NEW-LINE==That's so true.==NEW-LINE==That's for sure.==NEW-LINE==I agree 100%==NEW-LINE==I couldn't agree with you more.==NEW-LINE==(informal) Tell me about it! / You're telling me!==NEW-LINE==(informal) I'll say!==NEW-LINE==I suppose so. (use this phrase for weak agreement – you agree, but reluctantly)==NEW-LINE==
I'm not so sure about that.==NEW-LINE==That's not how I see it.==NEW-LINE==Not necessarily==NEW-LINE==
Oh no…==NEW-LINE==That's terrible.==NEW-LINE==Poor you. (Use this to respond to bad situations that are not too serious)==NEW-LINE==I'm so sorry to hear that.==NEW-LINE==

Are you free… [Saturday night?]==NEW-LINE==Are you doing anything… [Saturday night?]==NEW-LINE==. (informal) Do you wanna… [see a movie?]==NEW-LINE==(formal)Would you like to… [join me for dinner?]==NEW-LINE==

I'm starving! (= I'm very hungry)==NEW-LINE==Let's grab a bite to eat.==NEW-LINE==How about eating out tonight? (eat out = eat at a restaurant)==NEW-LINE==I'll have… (use this phrase for ordering in a restaurant)==NEW-LINE==

It cost a fortune.==NEW-LINE==It cost an arm and a leg.==NEW-LINE==That's a rip-off. (= overpriced; far more expensive than it should be)==NEW-LINE==That's a bit pricey.==NEW-LINE==That's quite reasonable. (= it's a good price)==NEW-LINE==That's a good deal. (= a good value for the amount of money)==NEW-LINE==It was a real bargain.==NEW-LINE==It was dirt cheap. (= extremely inexpensive)==NEW-LINE==
It's a little chilly.==NEW-LINE==It's freezing. (= extremely cold)==NEW-LINE==Make sure to bundle up. (bundle up = put on warm clothes for protection against the cold)==NEW-LINE==
It's absolutely boiling! (boiling = extremely hot)==NEW-LINE==it scorching hot outside==NEW-LINE==
I'm exhausted.==NEW-LINE==I'm dead tired.==NEW-LINE==I'm beat==NEW-LINE==I can hardly keep my eyes open==NEW-LINE==I'm gonna hit the sack. (hit the sack = go to bed)==NEW-LINE==
